BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:pee-workshop-matter-out-of-place-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260709T154201Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260810
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260811
SUMMARY:Deadline: Open Call: Pee Workshop (Matter Out of Place)
DESCRIPTION:Pee Workshop is looking for 16 performers to take part in a two
 -day research practice led by Nica Roses and Eris Kyriakides as part of th
 e dance and performance event Matter Out of Place. The workshop uses drink
 ing\, holding\, and releasing liquid as a starting point for choreographic
  research\, paying attention to the body's internal timing: what we consum
 e\, how liquid moves through the body\, what the bladder signals\, and how
  the organs produce movements that often go unnoticed. This cycle becomes 
 the structure of the research\, opening into dance\, somatic exercises\, c
 horeographic tasks\, group compositions\, and experiments with collective 
 energy. The material develops through urination but also through the share
 d experience of moving\, waiting\, responding\, and performing together. P
 erformers\, dancers\, movement practitioners\, and artists interested in s
 omatic research\, experimental choreography\, and collective performance-m
 aking are welcome\; professional dance training is not required\, but appl
 icants should feel comfortable working physically and collaboratively. All
  exercises are approached through clear consent\, respect for personal bou
 ndaries\, and collective care. The workshop takes place Monday 17 and Tues
 day 18 August 2026 from 10:00 to 17:00 at The Dirty Art Foundation\, culmi
 nating in an optional 60-minute public showing on Wednesday 19 August. Eac
 h performer receives a fee of EUR 200. To apply\, send a short introductio
 n about yourself\, your movement or performance experience\, and why you a
 re interested in the workshop to nicaxroses@gmail.com by 10 August 2026.\n
 \nOrganisation: Nica Roses & Eris Kyriakides\, at The Dirty Art Foundation
 \nLocation: The Dirty Art Foundation (Amsterdam\, Netherlands)\nAward: Per
 former fee of EUR 200. Participation in the optional public showing is not
  required to receive the fee.\nDuration: Two-day workshop\, Monday 17 and 
 Tuesday 18 August 2026\, 10:00-17:00\, with an optional 60-minute public s
 howing on Wednesday 19 August\n\nMore: https://www.instagram.com/p/DacdGWT
 jTSL/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.instagram.com/p/DacdGWTjTSL/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugr
 antdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:The Dirty Art Foundation (Amsterdam\, Netherlands)
END:VEVENT
