DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260731
SUMMARY:Deadline: Mondriaan Fund: Publication
DESCRIPTION:The Mondriaan Fund's Publication grant supports the production 
 of special publications about living visual artists from the Netherlands o
 r the Caribbean part of the Kingdom. It funds books and other publications
  that give substantial\, high-quality attention to an artist's work and pr
 actice. WHO CAN APPLY: visual artists and publishers\, individually or joi
 ntly\; the featured artist(s) must be professional and have been active fo
 r at least one year\, based in the Netherlands or the Caribbean part of th
 e Kingdom. AMOUNT: the Mondriaan Fund contributes a maximum of 35% of the 
 eligible expenses\; the available budget for this round is EUR 205\,000. A
 PPLYING: submitted through the Mondriaan Fund's online application portal\
 , which requires a pre-created account (allow several working days to set 
 up). DEADLINE: 30 July 2026\, 16:00 Dutch time (10:00 Caribbean time).\n\n
 Organisation: Mondriaan Fund (Mondriaan Fonds)\nLocation: Netherlands. Fea
 tured artist(s) must be professional visual artists based in the Netherlan
 ds or the Caribbean part of the Kingdom\; publishers may co-apply.\nAward:
  Contribution of up to 35% of eligible expenses. Total budget for this rou
 nd is EUR 205\,000.\nDuration: Project-based (production of a publication)
 .\n\nMore: https://www.mondriaanfonds.nl/en/apply-for-a-grant/grants/publi
 cation-2/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.mondriaanfonds.nl/en/apply-for-a-grant/grants/publication-2
 /?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Netherlands. Featured artist(s) must be professional visual artist
 s based in the Netherlands or the Caribbean part of the Kingdom\; publishe
 rs may co-apply.
END:VEVENT
