DTSTAMP:20260709T154201Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260827
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260828
SUMMARY:Deadline: Mondriaan Fund: Residency
DESCRIPTION:The Mondriaan Fund's Residency grant supports professional visu
 al artists\, curators\, and art observers who want to deepen their practic
 e through a residency in the Netherlands or abroad. It contributes to the 
 costs of a self-arranged residency that offers meaningful development for 
 the applicant's work. WHO CAN APPLY: visual artists\, curators\, and art o
 bservers who have been professionally active for at least one year and are
  based in the Netherlands or the Caribbean part of the Kingdom. AMOUNT: th
 e grant amount varies depending on the residency's location and duration\;
  applicants must contribute at least 10% of the costs themselves\, through
  personal investment\, third-party contributions\, an interest-free loan\,
  or crowdfunding. APPLYING: submitted through the Mondriaan Fund's online 
 application portal\, which requires a pre-created account (allow several w
 orking days). DEADLINE: 27 August 2026\, 16:00 Dutch time (11:00 Caribbean
  time).\n\nOrganisation: Mondriaan Fund (Mondriaan Fonds)\nLocation: Nethe
 rlands. Applicants must be based in the Netherlands or the Caribbean part 
 of the Kingdom\; residencies may take place in the Netherlands or abroad.\
 nAward: Grant amount varies depending on the location and duration of the 
 residency. Applicants must contribute at least 10% themselves (personal in
 vestment\, third-party contributions\, an interest-free loan\, or crowdfun
 ding).\nDuration: Varies by residency.\n\nMore: https://www.mondriaanfonds
 .nl/en/apply-for-a-grant/grants/residency/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugra
 ntdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.mondriaanfonds.nl/en/apply-for-a-grant/grants/residency/?ut
 m_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Netherlands. Applicants must be based in the Netherlands or the Ca
 ribbean part of the Kingdom\; residencies may take place in the Netherland
 s or abroad.
END:VEVENT
